    "description": "Lightweight local semantic-breadth linear classifier mapping per-segment blind features to common English ASL glosses. Weights are still WLASL/MS-ASL-inspired priors rather than learned ONNX weights, but the head now combines hierarchical family-conditioned softmax with generic motif, phase, and weak-margin priors so uncertain narrative-like segments can choose broader discourse/person/temporal/cognition glosses instead of collapsing only to concrete tool/action words. Round 13 sharpens the softmax calibration for the broader vocab so useful segment confidence recovers without changing the transcript ranking or low-margin warning. Local inference only; no raw video, no remote calls.",
